1.What information we collect
We will only collect the following information that is necessary for the purpose of providing our Services. You may not be able to enjoy our Services to the full extent if such information is not provided.
1.1 Information you provide to us
Registration Information. Information you provide to us when sign up for an account for the Games, including email address, age, character name, account password, and other information that help us confirm your access to your account and information we import from your connected social media account (Facebook, Google, Twitter and etc.), such as you account’s username and avatar on such social media and related device information.
Information you provide while using our Services. When you set up your profile for the Games or participate in our promotional activities, or you contact us via our customer service, you may provide your name, phone number, home address or other related game information such as game character ID, game character nickname, account ID.
We may need to collect your personal data for certain specific purposes and as permitted by applicable data protection law, including:
we may need to collect your location information so that we can provide specific Games' functions to you. For example, you can play or chat together with your nearby team members when you use our location-related functions.
1.2 Information we may collect or generate when you use our Services
To make our Services more convenient to you, we may collect certain data as the service log when you use the Services, this include:
details about your use of our Services, such as date and time stamps of actions and Game data, which includes your game level, progress, scores, achievements, game logs and interactions with other users;
details about your device, such as your device model, operating system, hardware and software versions, available storage space, browser type, device ID, IMEI number, MAC address, IP address, Bluetooth signals, language, time zone, storage and network access permission etc.;
details about your general location from your IP address or information about nearby Wi-Fi access points, beacons, and cell towers; or the details about your precise location with your GPS information when you use location-related functions of our Services (such as play or chat together with your nearby team members), but only when you provide affirmative, opt-in consent within the Services;
information you allow us to receive through device settings you turn on, such as access to your camera,photos or microphone;
communication logs including the content that you communicate with other users in the Game, and your interaction with us, for example when you use chat services (audio and/or text) to deliver your messages to other users or use in-app support to communicate with us;
error logs, error codes and error descriptions and other information that we generate relating to faults experienced by you;
We also collect information on your use of the Services via Cookies and related technologies (e.g., third-party SDKs). Information about our use of Cookies is provided below;
Our security feature will collect device information including OAID, IDFV, Android ID and a list of installed APK and running apps when you are using the Game;
You may receive push notifications with your consent or with option-out right based on your device operation system. The notification may update your game status and changes to you in time. You could opt in or out in this news notification through your mobile device’s operating system; and
other relevant information that we collect with your prior consent such as your friends list, group list information in the Game.
1.3 Information from other sources
We may collect your information contained in the information shared by other users, such as photos or videos published by other users which may contain your information.
We may obtain information about you from business partners, contractors, and other third parties and add it to our account information or other information we have collected.
2. How we use the information collected
We will use your personal data to provide, personalize and improve our Services in the following ways:
to help you set-up and manage your account of our Services;
to manage our Services and your use of our Services, such as to allow you to download and install the Game on your device; to detect your network and device status when you are playing the Game; and to correct bugs or errors that occur when you are playing the Game;
to provide security and functional updates, technical and other customer support for our Services, including considering and handling any complaints or questions that you raise;
to process purchase/refund orders and payment transactions of our Services;
to provide certain location-based services with your location data, such as a country-based version of the Game and the functionality of “forming a team with people nearby”;
to allow you to share content relating to our Services on social media;
to improve or personalized our Services for you or develop new ones;
to protect against and prevent fraud, and other legal or information security risks;
to conduct market research in relation to our Services;
to facilitate internal purposes such as auditing, data analysis, and research to improve our Services, user experience and customer communications;
to comply with legal and regulatory obligations and to exercise or defend our legal rights; and
to inform you of our promotional activities and any rewards you are entitled to, new product or service information and new features or enhancements to our Services that you may be interested in. We may require your consent for these marketing activities. In such cases where consent is required, we will only conduct the marketing activities if we have obtained your consent. You may opt out of receiving marketing communications from us at any time.
We are allowed to use your personal data in these ways because one or more of the following apply:
the processing is necessary so that we can provide you with our Services;
we have legal and regulatory obligations that we have to discharge;
we may need to in order to establish, exercise or defend our legal rights or for the purpose of legal proceedings;
the use of your personal data as described is necessary for our legitimate business interests, such as:
conducting market research in relation to our products and services, whereby legally permissible;
improving the Services that we provide;
making our communications or the content that we provide to you more relevant to you;
minimising our risks, for example, in relation to credit or fraud; and
developing our training process and systems; or
you have given your consent to certain types of processing. For example, you may have consented to receive marketing messages from us.
3. Use of Cookies
We use cookies and other similar technologies (“Cookies”) to enhance your experience using the Services. Cookies are computer files that are saved to your device and which may store information about you, your device, and that may be used to transmit that information to us. For example, Cookies are used to identify your device and record the visit so that we can allow you access to your account without requiring you to re-enter the information.
You can choose to permit installation of such Cookies or disable them. You may accept all Cookies, or instruct the device (in the case of the Game) or web browser (in the case of the Website) to provide notice at the time of installation of Cookies, or refuse to install Cookies. Although you are not required to accept Cookies when you use our Services, if you set your device to reject Cookies, you may not be able to enjoy all of the features and functionality of the Game.
You are able to opt out of accepting Cookies as below or other useful ways you may experience through third-party products. Most devices (in the case of mobile applications) and browsers (e.g. web apps and pages) allow you to change your Cookies settings. These settings will typically be found in the “options” or “preferences” menu of your browser. In order to understand these settings, the following links may be helpful, otherwise you should use the “Help” option in your browser for more details.
For Cookies in Android and in Chrome for web, you can try to opt out by resetting the privacy settings of your Android device system or via
https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647?co=GENIE.Platform%3DDesktop&hl=en;
For Cookies in iOS and in Safari web, you can opt out by resetting the privacy settings of your iOS device and selecting "block all cookies" or
https://support.apple.com/en-gb/guide/safari/sfri11471/mac;
For Cookies on other website, you can manage your Cookies preferences by using your own browser settings (for example, Edge, Internet Explorer, Firefox) to accept or block some or all Cookies or receive notice so you can consent to Cookies.
For Residents of the United States Only
The Network Advertising Initiative (a self-regulatory association comprised of third-party digital advertising companies) also offers a means to opt-out of a number of advertising Cookies. Please visit https://www.networkadvertising.org to learn more. Note that opting-out does not mean you will no longer receive online advertising. It does mean that the company or companies from which you opted-out will no longer deliver advertisements tailored to your preferences and usage patterns.
At this time, our Website does not recognise automated browser signals regarding tracking mechanisms, which may include “Do Not Track” instructions.
4. Information Accuracy
When you provide personal data to us, you agree to provide accurate information only, and agree that we may assume its accuracy and rely on it. If we provide means for you to update your information, you agree to update the information to keep it accurate.
5. Security
The Company is committed to protecting the security of your personal data. We use a variety of industry-standard security technologies and procedures to help protect your personal data from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. The Company has strict restrictions on access to user data. Unfortunately, no method of transmission over the Internet, or method of electronic storage, is completely secure. Although we will do our best to protect your personal data, we cannot guarantee the security of the information transmitted to our services.
