7. Your rights in relation to your personal data
You are entitled to a series of rights in relation to your personal data according to the applicable data protection laws, including the following.
Right to be informed
: you have the right to obtain information regarding the processing of your personal data by us.
Right to access:
you have the right to access your personal data which have been collected concerning you to figure out how we use and share it.
Right to withdraw consent:
you have the right to withdraw your consent to our processing of your personal data at any time. Please note, however, that we may still be entitled to process your personal data if we have another legitimate reason (other than consent) for doing so.
Right of rectification:
you have the right to have your personal data rectified if it is inaccurate or incomplete.
Right of erasure:
you have the right to have your personal data erased in certain circumstances. Please note that there may be circumstances where you ask us to erase your personal data, but we are legally entitled to retain it. If there is any other personal information you believe we process that you would like us to erase, please contact us in related app or sending your request to privacy@qoolandgames.com.
Right of objection or restriction:
You have the right to require us to stop or restrict processing the personal data we hold about you in certain circumstances. Again, there may be circumstances where you object to, or ask us to restrict, our processing of your personal data but we are legally entitled to continue processing your personal data and / or to refuse that request.
Right to data portability:
you have the right to receive a copy of the personal data concerning you, in a structured, commonly used and machine-readable format. You also have the right to request us to transmit that personal data to another controller where this is technically feasible. Please note that this right only applies to personal data which you have provided to us. Subject to applicable laws, we may not be able to provide you with personal data if providing it would interfere with our and/or other parties’ legitimate rights (e.g., where providing the personal data we hold about you would reveal information about another person to whom we shall fulfill our confidentiality and/or personal data protection obligations; where providing the personal data would adversely impact our legitimate interests protected by applicable laws, such as our trade secrets or intellectual property).
Right to complain:
you have the right to lodge a complaint with the data protection regulator, if you think that any of your rights have been infringed by us.
You can exercise your rights by contacting us using the details set out in the“Contacting us and making a complaint”section below.
We may need to confirm your identity before completing your request, and, for example, may ask for you to confirm data points we already have about you. We will only use personal data provided under this circumstance to verify the requestor’s identity or authority to make the request.
