9. Protection of Minors
Our Service is not intended for children. But we also attach great importance to the protection of personal data of minors. We will not knowingly collect any personal data about children under specific age (“Age of Consent”) (subject to different applicable laws, different Age of Consent would apply. For example, in the European Economic Area, the Age of Consent means 16 years old; in the United States, the Age of Consent means 13 years old) without making it clear that such information should only be provided with parental consent, if this is required by applicable laws. Qooland Games will only use the personal data of children as far as is permitted by law where the required parental or guardian consent has been obtained. If you are the parent or guardian of a child under Age of Consent, and in the event that you permit your child to use our Services you hereby agree to this Privacy Policy on behalf of yourself and your child, and you understand and agree that you will be responsible for all uses of the Services by your child whether or not such uses are authorized by you. If you believe that we have unintentionally collected your children’s personal information without your consent or want to withdraw your consent, you may request the deletion of the information by contacting us at privacy@qoolandgames.com.
For Residents of the United States Only
Consistent with the requirements of the U.S. Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act and to ensure that we act in accordance with other applicable laws, on any child-targeted site or application, or in any instance where we ask for age and determine the user is age 13 or under, we will ask for a consent of parent or guardian before we collect any personal information from the child.
Parents or guardians are entitled to exercise any rights that their children may have in relation to their personal information. For example, at any time, parents or guardians may review their children’s personal information, direct us to delete their children’s personal information, and may refuse to allow any further collection or use of the children’s personal information (in all cases subject to the requirements and restrictions set out in the applicable law). Please keep in mind that a request to delete records may lead to a termination of our services in our Game. Parents and guardians may also agree to the collection and use of their children’s personal information, but still not allow disclosure to third parties unless it’s part of the requested service. Parents and guardians can contact us through the “Contacting us and making a complaint” section to exercise their rights. To protect children’s privacy and security, we will take reasonable steps to help verify a parent’s identity before granting access to any personal information.
